## Step 2 — Run the mode VBS

Use the version-aware variant selector to pick the right VBS for the active
SAP system, then token-substitute and run via 32-bit cscript:

```powershell
$skillDir  = '<SKILL_DIR>'
$workTemp  = '{WORK_TEMP}'
$mode      = 'THE_MODE'
$paramsMap = @{ {{PARAM_MAP_HINT}} }   # populated from Step 1 parsing

# Ask the shared selector for the best-matching variant for the current
# active-session pin. Falls back to default sap_<name>_<mode>.vbs if no
# variant matches. The base name (no .vbs, no version tag) is what we pass.
$variantPath = & "<SAP_DEV_CORE_SHARED_DIR>\scripts\sap_select_vbs_variant.ps1" `
    -ReferencesDir "$skillDir\references" `
    -BaseName "sap_{{SKILL_NAME_LOWER}}_$mode"
if ($LASTEXITCODE -ne 0 -or -not $variantPath) {
    Write-Error "no VBS variant available for mode=$mode; see selector output"
    exit 1
}

$content = Get-Content $variantPath -Raw
foreach ($k in $paramsMap.Keys) {
    $content = $content.Replace("%%$k%%", $paramsMap[$k])
}

# Phase 3.5 session-attach plumbing (mandatory per parallel_safe_session_attach.md):
# %%SESSION_PATH%% is left empty here so AttachSapSession falls through to
# the SAPDEV_SESSION_PATH env var (set below). %%ATTACH_LIB_VBS%% gets the
# absolute path to the shared attach helper.
$content = $content -replace '%%SESSION_PATH%%', ''
$content = $content -replace '%%ATTACH_LIB_VBS%%', '<SAP_DEV_CORE_SHARED_DIR>\scripts\sap_attach_lib.vbs'
. '<SAP_DEV_CORE_SHARED_DIR>\scripts\sap_connection_lib.ps1'
$env:SAPDEV_SESSION_PATH = Get-SapCurrentSessionPath -WorkTemp '{WORK_TEMP}'

Set-Content "$workTemp\{{SKILL_NAME}}_run.vbs" $content -Encoding Unicode

C:/Windows/SysWOW64/cscript.exe //NoLogo "$workTemp\{{SKILL_NAME}}_run.vbs"
```

Read the script's stdout. Last line is `DONE` (success) or `ERROR: <text>`
(failure).

**Why the selector?** This skill was scaffolded on a specific SAP release
(see "Probed against" above). Other releases may move screens or menus.
Shipping additional variants is the supported path:

| Filename | When the selector picks it |
|---|---|
| `sap_{{SKILL_NAME_LOWER}}_<mode>.vbs` | default — used when no tagged variant matches |
| `sap_{{SKILL_NAME_LOWER}}_<mode>.<release>.vbs` | when the active pin's `server_release_marker` matches `<release>` |
| `sap_{{SKILL_NAME_LOWER}}_<mode>.<release>_GUI<MN>.vbs` | when both axes match (highest priority) |
| `sap_{{SKILL_NAME_LOWER}}_<mode>.GUI<MN>.vbs` | when only the GUI version matches |

